The paper is about image quality assessment (IQA) using deep neural networks (DNNs), which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of active learning and fine-tuning, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of human-rated databases and ground truth quality annotations, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
